<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 02 at 1:54PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Texas,
southern Cimarron, western Sherman, Dallam, northwestern Moore and
northern Hartley Counties through 230 PM CDT...
At 154 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Dalhart, moving north at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Dalhart, Stratford, Boise City, Texline, Wheeless, Ware, Felt, Conlen
and Griggs.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for the Panhandle
of Texas.</instruction>
